	h2 Street
	.story After surfing, we went for a stroll around the Kuta town. Not long after, we found ourselves in a shopping mall that looks like it came out of the same assembly line of the malls in Singapore called the Beach Walk Shopping Centres. It had all the popular major brands. At that moment, we were more interested in food and spotted Johnny Rockets. It was colorful and it served hamburgers. Our stomach made the decision and we went in for lunch. The burgers were good - lots of cheese, a thick slab of beef patty, fries and soda. All these for a weekday promotional price of SGD $10. After a heavy lunch, we went for a stroll. There were many small streets around lined with shops, hotels, restaurants, houses and temples. The shops sold craft items.
